cs, civilians and the military, and technology and tactics. Clearly laying out the fundamentals of military organization and strategy, Machiavelli marshals a veritable armory of precepts, prescriptions, and examples about such topics as how to motivate your soldiers and demoralize the enemy's, avoid ambushes, and gain the tactical and strategic advantage in countless circumstances. To help readers better appreciate the Art of War, Lynch provides an insightful introduction that covers its historical and political context, sources, influence, and contemporary relevance. He also includes a substantial interpretive essay discussing the military, political, and philosophical aspects of the work, as well as maps, an index of names, and a glossary.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  astrategy, military organization, tactics, technology, civilians, politics, war, philosophy, power, government, nonfiction, soldiers, napoleon, frederick the great, history, theory, advantage, ambush, demoralization, enemy, motivation, engineering, recruitment, orders, militia, ancient rome, artillery, necessity, failure, pikemen, cavalry, science.1 aLynch, Christopher.40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226500324423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226500324/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles